% Epistemic-model influence for the faithful-or-refuse contract (I0). REA is an
% agent-facing reverse-engineering toolkit whose Evidence model keeps three
% distinct categories â€” observation, inference, and unknown â€” and, crucially,
% "treats omitted evidence as unknown rather than equivalent"; its comparison
% engine labels every difference a *behavior candidate* instead of inferring
% equivalence from co-change. flowref borrows that discipline as a naming rule:
% the oracle's `INCOMPARABLE` (refused lift) is an UNKNOWN, never a false
% `EQUIVALENT`, and the oracle's `EQUIVALENT` is a *sampled-domain observation*
% (boundary battery + random sweep in `EquivCheck.lean`), distinct from a
% machine-checked Lean *proof*. See the "epistemic categories" durable rule in
% CHANGELOG.md.
@software{morluto2026rea,
  author    = {{morluto}},
